  "prompt": "I have a very old account in central bank in which no mobile number is registered. How to register my mobile number now?",
  "response": "Registering a mobile number with your old central bank account is important for enhancing the security of your account and enabling features like two-factor authentication (2FA). Here's a general guide on how to proceed:\n\n1. **Visit the Official Website:**\n   - Go to the official website of your country's central bank.\n   - Look for sections like \"Account Management,\" \"Customer Support,\" or \"Services.\"\n\n2. **Log Into Your Account:**\n   - Use your existing credentials to log into your account. If you\u2019ve forgotten your login details, follow the instructions for account recovery.\n\n3. **Navigate to Profile or Security Settings:**\n   - Once logged in, find the section where you can update personal information. This is often labeled as \"Profile,\" \"My Account,\" or \"Security Settings.\"\n\n4. **Add or Update Mobile Number:**\n   - Look for an option to add or update your mobile number.\n   - Enter your current mobile number in the designated field. You may need to verify it through a code sent via SMS.\n\n5. **Verify Your Identity:**\n   - You might be required to provide additional identification to ensure the security of your account. This could include answering security questions, providing identification documents, or using existing security measures like email verification.\n\n6. **Confirm the Update:**\n   - After entering and verifying your mobile number, make sure to save or confirm the changes.\n   - You might receive a confirmation message or email indicating that your mobile number has been successfully updated.\n\n7. **Enable Two-Factor Authentication (Optional but Recommended):**\n   - If available, enable 2FA to add an extra layer of security to your account using your mobile number.\n\n8. **Contact Customer Support if Needed:**\n   - If you encounter any issues while trying to update your mobile number online, reach out to the central bank\u2019s customer support.\n   - This can typically be done via phone, email, or through an online contact form available on the website.\n\n9. **Visit a Local Branch (If Applicable):**\n   - In some cases, especially with older accounts, you might need to visit a local branch of the central bank in person.\n   - Bring any necessary identification documents to facilitate the update.\n\n10. **Check for Confirmation:**\n    - After successfully updating your mobile number, ensure you receive a confirmation via SMS or email.\n    - Test the new mobile number by performing a small action that triggers a notification, such as a password reset.\n\n**Additional Tips:**\n\n- **Security First:** Always ensure that you are on the official website of your central bank to avoid phishing scams. Look for secure connections (https) and verify the URL.\n  \n- **Update Other Information:** While updating your mobile number, consider reviewing and updating other personal information to keep your account current and secure.\n\n- **Keep Records:** Maintain records of any communications or confirmations received during this process for future reference.\n\nIf you provide the name of your country\u2019s central bank or more specific details, I could offer more tailored advice. Otherwise, following the general steps above should help you register your mobile number successfully.",
